- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition and natural language processing using deep learning techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel deep learning BCI system for speech recognition.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with brain signals and their interpretation using neural networks.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses CNNs for feature extraction and classification.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with speech signals and their interpretation.
